Speccylator Documentation
*************************

   The @{i}Speccylator@{ui} program emulates a Sinclair ZX Spectrum computer. It
is available for Motorola MC680x0-based Amiga computers only and is
copyrighted (C) 1993-1997 Richard Carlsson.


 @{" Distribution " Link "Distribution"}           What you are allowed to do with these files.

 @{" Introduction " Link "Introduction"}           What the program does (and does not).

 @{" Usage from Workbench " Link "Usage from Workbench"}   Running from the Amiga graphical user interface.

 @{" Usage from CLI " Link "Usage from CLI"}         Running from the Command Line Interface (shell).

 @{" Program operation " Link "Program operation"}      Menus, keys, features, etc.

Appendices:
 @{" Keyboard layout " Link "Keyboard layout"}        Amiga - ZX Spectrum keyboard correspondencies.

 @{" Snapshot files " Link "Snapshot files"}         The format of the project files.


@EndNode

@Node "Distribution" "Speccylator.guide/Distribution"
